The paper discusses the use of algorithmic software segmentation for surgical treatment planning and visualization of postoperative results in the cranio-maxillofacial complex. This involves the use of CT scans and image-based segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The paper also focuses on the practical feasibility and assessment of the segmentation approach, which involves statistical analysis and evaluation, falling under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper is related to medical imaging and clinical practice, which falls under the medical informatics (cs.MED) sub-category.
